    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1889-12-03T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1889-12-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="124" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d124">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Blaine</persName> to
                                    Mr. <persName type="to">Stevens</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 12.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1889-12-03">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 3,
                                        1889</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have received your No. 11 of the
                                14th ultimo, confirmatory of the statements of previous dispatches
                                touching the importance of retaining one or more of our naval
                                vessels in Hawaiian waters until after the elections of February
                                next.</p>
                <p>You were informed by instruction, No. 11 of the 16th ultimo, of the
                                action of the Secretary of the Navy in this regard.</p>
                <p>You can exhibit to the naval officers concerned copies of the
                                dispatches referred to, and will in general keep such officers
                                advised of any political events of importance.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">James G.
                                Blaine.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
